    <p>Asian Fes­ti­val Of Chil­dren’s Con­tent 2020</p>
    <p>The 11th edi­tion of the fes­ti­val moves on­line with the theme of Voy­ages. The more than 40 lo­cal and in­ter­na­tional speak­ers in­clude writers Mariko Na­gai, Minh Le and Trevor Lai, il­lus­tra­tor Robert Ale­jan­dro, ed­u­ca­tors Junko Yokota and Rushton Hur­ley, as well as key fig­ures in the me­dia con­tent and lit­er­ary in­dus­try. They will share their ex­pe­ri­ences and ef­forts in re­spond­ing to the pan­demic. The an­nual fes­ti­val pro­motes and ad­vo­cates the cre­ation, de­vel­op­ment and ap­pre­ci­a­tion of qual­ity Asian sto­ries for chil­dren and young adults. Or­gan­ised by the Sin­ga­pore Book Coun­cil.</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­mor­row & Sun, 9.30am -</p>
    <p>5pm AD­MIS­SION: $30 (one-day pass), $50/$60 (two-day pass)</p>
    <p>INFO: afcc.com.sg/2020/page/ about-afcc</p>


